creator: Charles Monroe Sheldon
description:
LibriVox recording of In His Steps (version 2 Dramatic Reading) by Charles Monroe Sheldon.
Read in English by David Olson; Beth Thomas; Larry Wilson; Esther ben Simonides; Adele de Pignerolles; Glenn Koster, Jr.; Ashur Gharavi; Donald Gilmore; Mike Justice; Rupert Holliday; Rquade; Dave Harrell; Lydia; Gideon Snow; Bill; Kimberly Krause; Kristin Gjerløw; TriciaG; Maggie Travers; Rachel; Bob Scott; Bria Snow; John Burlinson

After a strange event at the Raymond First Church, Reverend Henry Maxwell asks his congregation a startling question: Will they pledge to try and do only what Jesus would for an entire year? Even more important, however is the question: Who will follow through the whole way? - Summary by Adele de Pignerolles

Narrated by: Glenn Koster, Jr. and Maggie Travers
Rev. Henry Maxwell: Larry Wilson
Mary Maxwell, Letter writer 4, Loreen, Rose Sterling, and Carlsen: Beth Thomas
Tramp and the Bishop: David Olson
Choir Soprano, Rachel Winslow, Girl 2, and Rough: Adele de Pignerolles
Choir Alto, Customer, Letter writer 2, Virginia Page, Mrs. Gray, Crowd Member 2, Female Crowd Member, Night Watchman, Auditorium Attendant, Mrs. Sterling, Mrs. Delano, Man 2, Divinity Student, and Third Speaker: Esther ben Simonides
Choir Tenor: Ashur Gharavi
Choir Bass and Stephen Clyde: Donald Gilmore
Dr. West, Jasper Chase and Burns: Mike Justice
Alexander Powers, Rollin Page, Crowd Member 1, Mr. Sterling, Clayton and First speaker: Rupert Holliday
Donald Marsh: Rquade
Edward Norman: Bill
Clark: Dave Harrell
Boy 1 and Servant: Lydia
George, Street Boy, and Crowd Member 3: Gideon Snow
Letter writer 1, Tent Meeting Attendee, Girl 1, Newspaper Correspondent, Messenger and Man in Crowd: Kimberly Krause
Madam Page, Mrs. Winslow, and Mrs. Bruce: Kristin Gjerløw
Mr. Gray: TriciaG
Fred Morris: Rachel
Milton Wright, Calvin Bruce, D.D., and Second Speaker: Bob Scott
Felicia Sterling: Bria Snow
Clarence Penrose: John Burlinson

Audio edited by: Adele de Pignerolles

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
